<subSubSection id="37E2657C4F23FFF6F0FAFD2FFD1F6C3F" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="7F4736F74F23FFF6F0FAFD2FFD1F6C3F" blockId="14.[192,1441,643,1051]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F23FFF6F0FAFD2FFDA06AFF" author="LaBerge, W. E. &amp; J. S. Moure" box="[240,565,707,732]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref13924" refString="LaBerge, W. E., and J. S. Moure. 1962. Type specimens of American eucerine bees deposited in the British Museum (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Boletim da Universidade do Parana, Zoologia 11: 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1962">LaBerge and Moure (1962)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F23FFF6F2EBFD2FFC136AFF" box="[737,902,707,731]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Melissodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifasciata">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F23FFF6F2EBFD2FFC136AFF" box="[737,902,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">M. trifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F23FFF6F3C0FD2FFAA66AFF" authority="F. Smith, 1854" authorityName="F. Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[970,1331,707,731]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Melissodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroaenea">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F23FFF6F3C0FD2FFBE26AFF" box="[970,1143,708,731]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">M. nigroaenea</emphasis>
F. 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F23FFF6F496FD28FAA66AFF" author="Smith, F." box="[1180,1331,707,731]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" pagination="199 - 465" refId="ref15654" refString="Smith, F. 1854. Catalogue of the hymenopterous insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part. 2. Apidae. British Museum; London. p. 199 - 465." type="book chapter" year="1854">Smith, 1854</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, an older name for a species from 
<collectingCountry id="07EF76674F23FFF6F1D5FD08FDB86ADF" box="[479,557,739,763]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, without offering additional comments. These authors furthermore designated a 
<typeStatus id="A04388554F23FFF6F12EFCE8FE016B3F" box="[292,404,771,795]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">lectotype</typeStatus>
female for 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F23FFF6F215FCEFFD456B3F" authorityName="F. Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[543,720,772,795]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Melissodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroaenea">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F23FFF6F215FCEFFD456B3F" box="[543,720,772,795]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">M. nigroaenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deposited in the Hope Department of Entomology, Oxford University. However, both species seem to be distinct (D. Urban, personal communication 2007), and are treated separately by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F23FFF6F1C0FCAFFD216B7F" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; D. Urban &amp; G. A. R. Melo" box="[458,692,835,859]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" refId="ref14912" refString="Moure, J. S., D. Urban, and G. A. R. Melo. 2007. Catalogue of bees (Hymenoptera: Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia; Curitiba. 1058 p." type="book" year="2007">Moure et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. On the other hand, LaBerge communicated to Snelling (R. R. Snelling, personal communication 1997) that “ 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F23FFF6F2F2FC8FFC3D6B5F" authorityName="F. Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[760,936,868,891]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Melissodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroaenea">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F23FFF6F2F2FC8FFC3D6B5F" box="[760,936,868,891]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">M. nigroaenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be limited to South America”. It would be useful to learn why these authors amended their earlier perspective. 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F23FFF6F46BFC6FFA356BBF" author="LaBerge, W. E. &amp; J. S. Moure" box="[1121,1440,899,924]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref13924" refString="LaBerge, W. E., and J. S. Moure. 1962. Type specimens of American eucerine bees deposited in the British Museum (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Boletim da Universidade do Parana, Zoologia 11: 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1962">LaBerge and Moure (1962)</bibRefCitation>
offered descriptive notes on the 
<typeStatus id="A04388554F23FFF6F23DFC48FD316B9F" box="[567,676,931,955]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="A04388554F23FFF6F2D1FC4FFCD26B98" box="[731,839,932,956]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">paratype</typeStatus>
females of 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F23FFF6F3C0FC4FFBE16B9F" authorityName="F. Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[970,1140,932,955]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Melissodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroaenea">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F23FFF6F3C0FC4FFBE16B9F" box="[970,1140,932,955]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">M. nigroaenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therein they mentioned some differences in hair coloration between that species and 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F23FFF6F3B8FC2FFBCF6BFF" box="[946,1114,963,987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Melissodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifasciata">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F23FFF6F3B8FC2FFBCF6BFF" box="[946,1114,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">M. trifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The authors offered little information on surface sculpturing which tends to be more reliable characters for species recognition. Here we treat both species as distinct.
</paragraph>
